dct_title_s: Insula Malta accuratissime delineata, urbibus et fortalitiis
dct_description_sm: Inset with a plan of Valetta to the lower right with a title cartouche above embellished with arms; numbered key to points of interest in upper right corner; ships throughout the Mediterranean.
Legends at the top right indicating city gates, isles, ports ...
Figurative illustration of ships. Compass rose.
Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.

Maltese archipelago and North African and Sicilian littoral, with key. Vignettes of multiple sea battles near the coasts of Sicily, Tripoli and Tunis. Insert of Valletta with fortifications. Probably from de Wit’s Atlas Major.
dct_creator_sm: Wit, Frederick De, art, print and map seller, publisher and engraver., 1629-1706
